WEBVTT

00:04.338 --> 00:05.339 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.372 --> 00:07.174 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.207 --> 00:10.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour": On this day
honoring Dr.
Martin Luther King Jr.,
president-elect Trump

00:10.711 --> 00:16.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
meets with King's son, despite a
war of words
with a surviving civil rights
leader, Congressman

00:16.817 --> 00:18.685 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
John Lewis.

00:18.719 --> 00:24.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: Mr. Trump makes waves
overseas, calling
NATO obsolete and signaling the
U.S. may ease

00:24.825 --> 00:27.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sanctions on Russia.

00:27.394 --> 00:33.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And one man's journey to
understand his hometown's
racist history leads to insights
into a still

00:33.834 --> 00:35.636 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
deeply divided America.

00:35.669 --> 00:37.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS, Author, "Blood
at the Root:
A Racial Cleansing in America":
We were raised

00:37.137 --> 00:40.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with this notion that, every
day, America
gets a little bit more just.

00:40.274 --> 00:46.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, in the research, I
learned that
some -- what that leaves out is
that sometimes

00:46.647 --> 00:49.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the gains of one generation are
given back
in the next.

00:49.650 --> 00:52.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:52.953 --> 00:57.257 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:57.291 --> 01:09.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Americans have
spent this day
honoring the life and legacy of
Dr. Martin

01:09.369 --> 01:11.171 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Luther King Jr.

01:11.204 --> 01:16.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It comes amid an open conflict
between another
iconic civil rights figure and
the nation's

01:16.610 --> 01:18.979 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
new leader.

01:19.012 --> 01:23.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President-elect Trump marked the
King holiday
by inviting the civil rights
leader's son

01:23.317 --> 01:25.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to his New York tower.

01:25.585 --> 01:31.425 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Martin Luther King III called it
a very constructive
meeting, and quoted the
president-elect, saying

01:31.458 --> 01:33.327 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he wants to reach out to all
Americans.

01:33.360 --> 01:37.097 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTIN LUTHER KING III,
President &amp; CEO, Realizing
the Dream: I believe that that's
his intent.

01:37.130 --> 01:41.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think also that we have to
consistently
engage with pressure, public
pressure.

01:41.969 --> 01:43.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It doesn't happen automatically.

01:43.770 --> 01:48.041 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
My father and his team
understood that, did
that, and I think that Americans
are prepared

01:48.075 --> 01:49.876 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to do that.

01:49.910 --> 01:53.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: King steered
clear of the Trump
feud with a civil rights hero,
Democratic

01:53.880 --> 01:55.849 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Representative John Lewis of
Georgia.

01:55.882 --> 02:00.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN LUTHER KING III: I think
that, in the
heat of emotion, a lot of things
get said

02:00.287 --> 02:02.089 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on both sides.

02:02.122 --> 02:07.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The war of words
began Friday,
with Lewis telling NBC that
Trump's election

02:07.694 --> 02:10.998 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wasn't legitimate because of
Russian meddling.

02:11.031 --> 02:12.632 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The full interview aired Sunday.

02:12.666 --> 02:14.301 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:14.334 --> 02:17.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN LEWIS (D), Georgia: I don't
see this
president-elect as a legitimate
president.

02:17.871 --> 02:22.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lewis also said
he will boycott
Friday's inauguration.

02:22.409 --> 02:27.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All told, more than two dozen
members of Congress
now say they will do the same.

02:27.447 --> 02:32.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect fired back
at Lewis over
the weekend, tweeting that he
should spend

02:32.619 --> 02:39.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- quote -- "more time on
helping his district
and calling him all talk, talk,
talk, no action

02:39.693 --> 02:41.028 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or results."

02:41.061 --> 02:45.665 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On CBS this weekend, vice
president-elect
Pence also pushed back.

02:45.699 --> 02:48.301 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE PENCE (R), Vice
President-Elect: To make
a comment that he did not
consider Donald

02:48.335 --> 02:51.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Trump to be a legitimate
president, I think
is deeply disappointing.

02:51.405 --> 02:57.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I believe inaugurations are a
moment when
we should come together around
that individual

02:57.444 --> 03:01.615 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who has been elected to be
president of the
United States of America.

03:01.648 --> 03:07.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Today, at a King
Day breakfast
in Miami, Lewis ignored the
Trump criticism.

03:07.587 --> 03:10.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, he issued a call to
action to his
listeners.

03:10.657 --> 03:11.625 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:11.658 --> 03:12.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN LEWIS: You must have
courage.

03:12.926 --> 03:15.562 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You must be bold.

03:15.595 --> 03:19.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And never, ever give up when you
know that
you're right.

03:19.800 --> 03:26.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For his part, Mr.
Trump canceled
an early plan to spend the
holiday in Washington

03:26.073 --> 03:30.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and visit the National Museum of
African American
History and Culture.

03:30.911 --> 03:37.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the vice president-elect was
in Washington
at the Martin Luther King Jr.
Memorial.

03:37.284 --> 03:43.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama, in his last
week in office,
took part in a service event at
a D.C. family

03:43.123 --> 03:44.891 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
shelter.

03:44.925 --> 03:48.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: There
was no sign
of a letup in another
confrontation, this

03:49.029 --> 03:52.132 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one between Mr. Trump and the
intelligence
community.

03:52.165 --> 03:57.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It started when outgoing CIA
Director John
Brennan said Sunday that the
president-elect

03:57.404 --> 04:01.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
must do more than -- quote --
"talk and tweet
about national security."

04:01.875 --> 04:04.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRIS WALLACE, Host, "Â®MD-BO /FOX
News Sunday":
Do you think that Mr. Trump
understands the

04:04.478 --> 04:06.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
threat from Russia?

04:06.446 --> 04:11.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BRENNAN, CIA Director: I
don't think
he has a full appreciation of
Russian capabilities,

04:11.518 --> 04:16.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia's intentions, and actions
that they
are undertaking in many parts of
the world.

04:16.156 --> 04:19.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's what the obligation
and responsibility
of the intelligence community
is.

04:19.292 --> 04:21.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Later, Mr. Trump
fired back
on Twitter.

04:21.862 --> 04:27.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He criticized the CIA's record
on conflicts
in Syria, Crimea and Ukraine.

04:27.200 --> 04:32.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, referring directly to
Brennan, he asked
-- quote -- "Was this the leaker
of fake news?"

04:32.939 --> 04:38.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect also raised
hackles across
Europe with critical comments
about NATO and

04:38.111 --> 04:39.312 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the European Union.

04:39.346 --> 04:42.782 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will turn to that story right
after the
news summary.

04:42.816 --> 04:48.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the domestic front, the
incoming president
now says he means to replace
Obamacare with

04:48.155 --> 04:50.157 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
insurance for everybody.

04:50.190 --> 04:54.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's told The Washington Post
that his plan
is nearly complete, and that it
will offer

04:54.694 --> 04:58.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
-- quote -- "much lower
deductibles," but
he offered no details.

04:58.798 --> 05:04.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Turkey, there is word that
police have
captured the man suspected of
killing 39 in

05:04.704 --> 05:08.208 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an Istanbul nightclub during New
Year's celebrations.

05:08.241 --> 05:12.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Islamic State group had
claimed responsibility
for the New Year's attack.

05:12.779 --> 05:15.949 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It triggered an intense
nationwide manhunt.

05:15.982 --> 05:21.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkish media reports say that
the Uzbek national
was taken into custody during a
raid in an

05:21.721 --> 05:23.757 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Istanbul suburb.

05:23.790 --> 05:29.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A Turkish cargo plane crashed
today in Kyrgyzstan,
destroying out half a village
and killing

05:29.796 --> 05:31.731 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at least 37 people.

05:31.765 --> 05:37.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Boeing 747 was trying to
land in dense
fog near the capital city,
Bishkek.

05:37.671 --> 05:41.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was no immediate word what
caused the
crash.

05:41.741 --> 05:46.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a startling new report
about wealth
inequality around the globe.

05:46.213 --> 05:52.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The anti-poverty organization
Oxfam reports
that the eight richest men on
Earth own as

05:52.519 --> 05:57.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
much as the poorest half of the
world's population.

05:57.324 --> 06:00.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's about 3.6 billion people.

06:00.160 --> 06:04.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The report says the gap has
grown from what
it was just a year ago by a
significant amount.

06:05.031 --> 06:08.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAX LAWSON, Oxfam: We have seen
countries
in the last 10 years that have
bucked the

06:08.101 --> 06:11.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trend and that are going in the
other direction,
and are reducing the gap between
rich and

06:11.972 --> 06:13.206 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
poor.

06:13.240 --> 06:15.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One thing they do is, they get
the rich to
pay their tax.

06:15.075 --> 06:20.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have got a situation where
billionaires
are paying less tax often than
their cleaner

06:20.080 --> 06:21.381 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or their secretary.

06:21.414 --> 06:22.382 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's crazy.

06:22.415 --> 06:24.484 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're seeing wealth channeled
upwards.

06:24.517 --> 06:30.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The report was
released ahead
of the World Economic Forum in
Davos, Switzerland.

06:30.624 --> 06:35.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ten more long-term detainees
have left the
U.S. prison at Guantanamo Bay,
Cuba.

06:35.729 --> 06:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Persian Gulf state of Oman
announced today
that it accepted the 10.

06:40.433 --> 06:44.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That leaves 45 prisoners
remaining at Guantanamo.

06:44.170 --> 06:47.073 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
President Obama has pushed to
close the prison.

06:47.107 --> 06:49.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President-elect Trump has vowed
to keep it
open.

06:49.909 --> 06:55.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Conservative commentator Monica
Crowley has
backed out of a job with the new
Trump administration,

06:55.915 --> 06:59.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
amid a plagiarism, an alleged
plagiarism scandal.

06:59.219 --> 07:04.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's widely reported that she's
decided against
serving at the National Security
Council.

07:04.724 --> 07:11.831 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Crowley is accused of
plagiarizing parts of
her doctoral dissertation and
her 2012 book.

07:11.865 --> 07:17.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The World Series champion
Chicago Cubs were
feted today by the White Sox fan
who calls

07:17.304 --> 07:19.072 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the White House home.

07:19.105 --> 07:23.777 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Cubs were the last
championship team that
Mr. Obama will greet while he's
in office.

07:23.810 --> 07:27.213 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They presented the 44th
president with two
special jerseys.

07:27.247 --> 07:33.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Cubs won the series last
November for
the first time since 1908.

07:33.720 --> 07:37.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
