died today
in Houston.

07:37.457 --> 07:40.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was the last of a dozen men
to walk on
the moon.

07:40.527 --> 07:42.996 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A handful of others still
survive.

07:43.029 --> 07:49.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Cernan commanded the Apollo 17
mission to
the lunar surface in December
1972.

07:49.035 --> 07:54.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In later years, he urged
Congress to approve
a return to the moon.

07:54.140 --> 07:57.644 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Eugene Cernan was 82 years old.

07:57.677 --> 08:03.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
our Politics
Monday duo previews inauguration
week; lessons

08:03.583 --> 08:16.196 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on race from a city that once
forced out its
black residents; and much more.

08:16.229 --> 08:24.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Beyond his social media
statements over the
weekend, the president-elect had
much more

08:24.471 --> 08:28.208 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to say in an interview with two
European publications.

08:28.241 --> 08:33.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He opined on the usefulness of
NATO and the
European Union, on the stability
of Germany

08:33.913 --> 08:37.817 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
under Chancellor Angela Merkel,
and on Brexit.

08:37.851 --> 08:39.753 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang begins our coverage.

08:39.786 --> 08:46.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
