with the Trump
assessment and said NATO's main
goal is confrontation.

09:48.254 --> 09:53.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it said little about the
president-elect's
suggestion that he might drop
U.S. sanctions

09:53.593 --> 09:57.797 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on Russia in exchange for
nuclear arms reductions.

09:57.831 --> 10:02.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Mr. Trump also said he's
indifferent about
the European Union's future in
the wake of

10:02.068 --> 10:07.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Britain's vote to leave it:
"Personally, I
don't think it matters much for
the United

10:07.440 --> 10:09.242 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
States.

10:09.275 --> 10:12.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Look, the E.U. was formed,
partially, to beat
the United States on trade, so I
don't really

10:12.946 --> 10:15.715 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
care whether it's separate or
together."

10:15.748 --> 10:20.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect had special
criticism
for German Chancellor Angela
Merkel.

10:20.320 --> 10:26.426 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He said she had made a
catastrophic mistake
in taking in thousands of
migrants and refugees.

10:26.459 --> 10:31.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he said he will start off
trusting Merkel
and Russian President Vladimir
Putin equally,

10:31.831 --> 10:34.234 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but said that may not last.

