for that relationship.

11:17.477 --> 11:22.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We get reaction to Mr. Trump's
comments from
two people with extensive
experience managing

11:22.515 --> 11:25.018 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
U.S.-European relations.

11:25.051 --> 11:26.586 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nicholas Burns was a career
diplomat.

11:26.619 --> 11:30.156 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was U.S. ambassador to NATO
during the
Obama administration.

11:30.189 --> 11:31.691 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's now at Harvard University.

11:31.724 --> 11:33.793 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he joins us tonight from
London.

11:33.826 --> 11:38.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here in studio, Heather Conley,
she was deputy
assistant secretary of state for
European

11:38.498 --> 11:42.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Eurasian affairs during the
George W.
Bush administration.

11:42.835 --> 11:47.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's now director and senior
fellow of the
Europe Program at the Center for
Strategic

11:47.874 --> 11:51.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and International Studies, a
think tank in
Washington, D.C.

11:51.811 --> 11:53.713 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Thank you both for joining us.

11:53.746 --> 11:57.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Burns, let me start with
you, former ambassador
to NATO.

11:57.984 --> 12:03.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump says that NATO is
obsolete because
it doesn't take on terror,
unfair to the United

12:03.756 --> 12:04.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
States.

12:04.757 --> 12:06.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What's your take?

12:06.593 --> 12:07.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICHOLAS BURNS, Former U.S.
Undersecretary
of State for Political Affairs:
He's completely

12:07.093 --> 12:08.528 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wrong about that.

12:08.561 --> 12:12.465 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was ambassador to NATO for
President George
W. Bush actually on 9/11.

12:12.498 --> 12:17.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on 9/11, when we were
attacked from al-Qaida
in Afghanistan, the NATO allies
came to us

12:17.604 --> 12:19.305 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Brussels.

12:19.339 --> 12:22.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said they wanted to invoke
Article V
of the NATO treaty, an attack on
one of us

12:22.141 --> 12:23.810 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is an attack on all of us.

12:23.843 --> 12:26.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They came to our defense big
time.

12:26.579 --> 12:28.114 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They all went into Afghanistan.

12:28.147 --> 12:32.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They bled, died and were wounded
for us in
Afghanistan.

12:32.518 --> 12:34.387 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're all still fighting in
Afghanistan.

12:34.420 --> 12:39.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We fought the terrorism of
al-Qaida and the
terrorism of the Taliban and
other terrorist

12:39.158 --> 12:40.226 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
groups in Afghanistan.

12:40.259 --> 12:42.829 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Trump is -- Donald Trump is
exactly wrong.

12:42.862 --> 12:47.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I can tell you, having been
in London
today, people here are just
flabbergasted

12:47.100 --> 12:49.902 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by this interview in The Times
in London.

12:49.936 --> 12:55.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To basically -- to denigrate
NATO as obsolete,
to root openly for the weakening
of the European

12:55.108 --> 13:01.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Union, to castigate Angela
Merkel, our strongest
friend in Europe, we have not
seen an American

13:01.581 --> 13:06.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president be so openly critical
of our allies
in 70 years.

13:06.819 --> 13:10.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And yet he doesn't criticize our
adversary
Vladimir Putin.

13:10.690 --> 13:12.525 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is mystifying.

13:12.558 --> 13:15.161 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People here are uncertain about
American leadership.

13:15.194 --> 13:18.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a very poor and unwise way
to start his
term in office.

13:18.498 --> 13:23.803 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Heather Conley, the
larger point,
your take on the remarks, but
also specifically

13:23.836 --> 13:25.738 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on NATO.

13:25.772 --> 13:29.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says it's unfair because the
other countries
aren't paying their fair share,
that the financial

13:29.942 --> 13:31.644 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
burden falls on the United
States.

13:31.678 --> 13:33.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HEATHER CONLEY, Director, Europe
Program,
Center for Strategic and
International Studies:

13:33.546 --> 13:37.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, it's certainly been a
bipartisan comment
to get European countries to
increase their

13:37.950 --> 13:39.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
defense spending.

13:39.886 --> 13:44.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's something that they
-- NATO countries
pledged two-and-a-half years ago
to substantially

13:44.891 --> 13:47.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
increase their defense spending,
and they're
doing that.

13:47.960 --> 13:54.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The challenge is, the United
States is safer
because NATO exists.

13:54.200 --> 14:00.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When we join with our allies to
-- whether
it's defeating the Taliban in
Afghanistan,

14:00.840 --> 14:10.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
supporting those in Iraq to beat
back ISIS,
to protect NATO when Russia
invades a neighboring

14:10.249 --> 14:12.852 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
country, this -- it makes
America stronger.

14:12.885 --> 14:14.654 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a part of U.S. national
security.

14:14.687 --> 14:19.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when you're criticizing NATO
and saying
it's obsolete, you're actually
degrading U.S.

14:19.559 --> 14:20.960 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
national security.

14:20.993 --> 14:25.431 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is what has us all so
confused about
Mr. Trump's comments.

14:25.465 --> 14:29.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's OK to say Europe is not
spending enough
and we need to increase that
spending.

14:29.869 --> 14:34.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we get an enormous benefit
out of the
NATO alliance.

14:34.474 --> 14:37.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Let's drill down on
the some of
the other things that he said in
the interview.

14:37.376 --> 14:42.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ambassador Burns, what about
this idea of
lifting sanctions on Russia
which were put

14:42.148 --> 14:47.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in place for their annexation of
Crimea in
exchange for an agreement on
arms reduction?

14:47.854 --> 14:51.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICHOLAS BURNS: It's hard to see
the logic
in this agreement.

14:51.457 --> 14:55.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everyone, of course, wants to
see nuclear
stability between the United
States and Russia.

14:55.628 --> 14:57.330 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's the highest priority.

14:57.363 --> 15:01.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we can achieve nuclear arms
stability
and reduction based on the
interest of both

15:01.801 --> 15:03.503 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
sides.

15:03.536 --> 15:06.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For Donald Trump to say, I will
do this, I
will reduce nuclear weapons with
Russia and

15:06.773 --> 15:11.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
