19:46.018 --> 19:47.753 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

19:47.787 --> 19:50.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: His team says that
he is still
working on the speech, still
refining it.

19:50.056 --> 19:54.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have no idea what that speech
will say,
though they promise he will talk
about bringing

19:54.760 --> 19:56.729 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Americans together.

19:56.762 --> 20:02.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he's also giving a speech
the night before
at sort of a pregame rally and
event for supporters.

20:02.701 --> 20:05.538 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, of course, there will
be protests
the following day.

20:05.571 --> 20:07.406 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What should we
look for, Susan?

20:07.440 --> 20:09.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE, Washington Bureau
Chief, USA Today:
I think this has been a
remarkable period

20:09.775 --> 20:17.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
since the president-elect won
the election
two months ago, because,
usually, this has

20:17.850 --> 20:22.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been a time when Americans kind
of come together,
there's this era of kind of good
feeling,

20:22.288 --> 20:23.622 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
at least for a little while.

20:23.656 --> 20:25.424 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We haven't seen that with this.

20:25.458 --> 20:28.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We have seen really a
continuation of the
rhetoric we heard during the
campaign, and

20:28.527 --> 20:30.329 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some of the divisions have
persisted.

20:30.362 --> 20:35.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Donald Trump is going to be
inaugurated
with the lowest approval ratings
of any president

20:35.134 --> 20:37.336 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
since we started to take polls.

20:37.369 --> 20:41.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this is going to be -- we
overuse the
word unprecedented when it comes
to Donald

20:41.207 --> 20:44.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump, but there are many ways
in which this
period of time has been
unprecedented.

20:44.110 --> 20:47.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And part of that,
as we have
been discussing and reporting
earlier in the

20:47.746 --> 20:51.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
program, Tam, is this back and
forth over
the weekend between Congressman
John Lewis,

20:51.917 --> 20:56.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who said he didn't view Donald
Trump as a
legitimately elected president
because of

20:56.088 --> 21:01.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Russian interference in the
election,
but then Mr. Trump's coming back
at him and

21:01.494 --> 21:03.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying, you should be doing more
in your own
district.

21:03.996 --> 21:05.764 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What are we to make of all that?

21:05.798 --> 21:08.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: And also saying
that he's all
talk, talk, talk, and no action,
which many

21:08.734 --> 21:15.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people took issue with, given
that John Lewis
is a civil rights hero, icon.

21:15.374 --> 21:22.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this is the latest instance
of which you
could basically go every single
week for the

21:22.214 --> 21:29.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
last year-and-a-half of Donald
Trump taking
a fight, you know, taking an
opportunity to

21:29.855 --> 21:34.293 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
strike back at someone on
Twitter, getting
into a Twitter feud.

21:34.326 --> 21:35.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Last week, it was Meryl Streep.

21:35.828 --> 21:37.663 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This week, it's John Lewis.

21:37.696 --> 21:42.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many times, he's gotten into
feuds with people
who you would consider to be
people that you

21:42.902 --> 21:46.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wouldn't want to touch, that,
politically,
it's just not worth going there.

21:46.372 --> 21:53.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Donald Trump, you know, he
will not just
sit back and let someone insult
him.

21:53.479 --> 21:58.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the way John Lewis did
insult him really
hit him in a soft spot.

21:58.317 --> 22:04.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Susan, is there
evidence that
this kind of response on the
part of the president-elect

22:04.190 --> 22:05.925 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
helps him in some way?

22:05.958 --> 22:09.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE: Well, it may help
him with his
core supporters who have elected
him maybe

22:09.695 --> 22:14.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in part because he is so
combative, because
he never fails to counterpunch
if he thinks

22:14.366 --> 22:16.068 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
somebody has taken a punch at
him.

22:16.101 --> 22:21.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And there are even some
defenders of John
Lewis who think Donald Trump is
still the

22:21.106 --> 22:24.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
legitimate president -- that's a
very serious
charge to make against someone
who is about

22:24.476 --> 22:30.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to take the oath of office --
but that he
is a figure of such respect, of
such iconic

22:30.316 --> 22:34.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
status in the United States from
the civil
rights struggle, that he was a
particularly

22:34.086 --> 22:36.021 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
inappropriate person to have a
counterpunch.

22:36.055 --> 22:42.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now we have more than two
dozen members
of Congress saying they will
boycott the inauguration

22:42.228 --> 22:43.963 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ceremonies.

22:43.996 --> 22:45.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, sometimes, member of
Congress I think
haven't shown up, because who
would notice

22:45.197 --> 22:46.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
if every member of the House was
there?

22:46.966 --> 22:52.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this has now become a
rallying cry and
another sign of the divisions
that Donald

22:52.304 --> 22:54.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump will face when he moves
into the White
House.

22:54.273 --> 22:58.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tamara, how much
should Donald
Trump, who is a Republican --
will be a Republican

22:58.077 --> 23:01.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president, be concerned about
his relationship
with the African-American
community?

23:01.614 --> 23:05.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, after all, this is not a
group of
voters who supported him.

23:05.351 --> 23:06.585 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Right.

23:06.619 --> 23:08.420 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And this continues.

23:08.454 --> 23:13.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
By about a little more than
two-thirds in
a new Pew poll of
African-Americans say that

23:13.092 --> 23:17.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they do not approve of the job
that Donald
Trump has been doing in his
transition of

23:17.296 --> 23:19.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
explaining his policies or where
he's going.

23:19.665 --> 23:23.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's far worse than he ranks
with white
voters, for instance.

23:23.068 --> 23:24.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, this is a problem.

23:24.637 --> 23:29.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a problem that Donald Trump
has, at least
on some level, tried to address.

23:29.875 --> 23:33.445 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He brought Steve Harvey to Trump
Tower.

23:33.479 --> 23:35.581 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He talks about wanting to help.

23:35.614 --> 23:39.752 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But almost always, he focuses
on, well, I
want to help urban centers.

23:39.785 --> 23:44.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to help crime-ridden
urban areas, which
many in the African-American
community have

23:44.657 --> 23:50.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been hearing him say throughout
the campaign,
and hearing it as an insult and
sort of misunderstanding

23:50.262 --> 23:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the fact that large numbers of
black people
live in the suburbs, for
instance, and are

23:53.899 --> 23:55.701 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
quite affluent.

23:55.734 --> 23:58.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, today, he
did meet with
the son of Dr. Martin Luther
King Jr., Susan.

23:58.170 --> 23:59.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SUSAN PAGE: He did.

23:59.972 --> 24:03.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, of course, this is -- this
would have
been, I think, the 88th of
Martin Luther King

24:03.142 --> 24:07.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jr., and so a good day to meet
with his son
and to think about some of the
issues that

24:07.980 --> 24:09.815 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Martin Luther King raised.

24:09.848 --> 24:13.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I want to
turn to something
else that Donald Trump said in
one of the

24:13.085 --> 24:16.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interviews he did over the
weekend with The
Washington Post -- and, Susan, I
will start

24:16.388 --> 24:20.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with you on this -- in which he
said, in so
many words, that he supports --
they were

24:20.225 --> 24:23.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
talking about health insurance
and what's
going to happen to Obamacare.

24:23.929 --> 24:27.499 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he said -- he promised
insurance for everyone.

24:27.533 --> 24:29.335 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How are we to interpret this?

24:29.368 --> 24:32.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE: So, a revelation, I
think, to
all of us, including
congressional Republicans

24:32.237 --> 24:34.239 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
who work on this issue.

24:34.273 --> 24:35.474 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Health care, what a tough issue.

24:35.507 --> 24:38.477 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We saw that with the passage of
the Affordable
Care Act.

24:38.510 --> 24:43.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in this interview with The
Washington
Post, Donald Trump said he would
have insurance

24:43.282 --> 24:48.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for everybody, it wouldn't be a
single-payer
system, it would be a great
system and less

24:48.721 --> 24:49.688 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
expensive.

24:49.722 --> 24:52.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, if that's true, that would
be terrific.

24:52.057 --> 24:55.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But people who work in health
care say that
is a really tough thing to do.

24:55.594 --> 25:00.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we think that it's possible
that he is
-- we're moving toward is health
care access

25:00.466 --> 25:01.834 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for all, not coverage for all.

25:01.867 --> 25:03.736 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Access.

25:03.769 --> 25:05.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE: Access to all is
something that
Paul Ryan, the House speaker,
has talked about.

25:05.571 --> 25:10.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that would still be an
achievement, but
an easier thing to do than
coverage for all.

25:10.109 --> 25:11.910 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Tam, I
wanted to ask you.

25:11.944 --> 25:15.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What Susan brought up is that
how does this
square with what Republicans
have been saying

25:15.481 --> 25:17.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they want to do about health
care?

25:17.149 --> 25:18.117 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAMARA KEITH: Right.

25:18.150 --> 25:19.551 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What she said, universal access.

25:19.585 --> 25:21.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a big difference between
coverage
for all and universal access.

25:21.954 --> 25:26.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one thing that Republicans
have talked
about a lot recently is how
President Obama

25:26.091 --> 25:29.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said, if you like your plan, you
can keep
your plan, if you like your
doctor, you can

25:30.028 --> 25:31.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
keep your doctor.

25:31.296 --> 25:34.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they point out that that
simply proved
not to be true.

25:34.733 --> 25:39.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Donald Trump and his team
are tiptoeing
very close to making promises
that in the

25:39.772 --> 25:44.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not-so-distant future could be
held against
them if it doesn't become a
reality.

25:44.476 --> 25:48.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think lots of people would
love to have
health insurance for everyone.

25:48.347 --> 25:51.383 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Many people would like to have
health insurance.

25:51.417 --> 25:57.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, you know, Donald Trump also
said that
he had a great plan for knocking
out ISIS,

25:57.890 --> 26:00.459 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and then he never really said
what that plan
was.

26:00.492 --> 26:02.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We will have to see.

26:02.227 --> 26:06.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says he has to wait for Tom
Price, his
health and human services agency
director,

26:06.465 --> 26:11.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be nom -- or to be confirmed,
and then
he says right away that plan
will be clear.

26:11.670 --> 26:13.572 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I think we have to wait to
see the plan.

26:13.605 --> 26:17.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And just finally,
in a few
seconds, Susan, his incoming
health and human

26:17.309 --> 26:22.080 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
services Cabinet
secretary-designate is in
a little bit of hot water right
now.

26:22.114 --> 26:25.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUSAN PAGE: That's right, a
story that CNN
first reported that he bought
some -- when

26:25.818 --> 26:30.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he was a member of Congress last
year, he
bought some stock in a bio-med
company, then

26:30.622 --> 26:35.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a week later introduced some
legislation that
would help that company, and
then got a campaign

26:35.360 --> 26:37.296 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
contribution from that company.

26:37.329 --> 26:41.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chuck Schumer , the Senate
Democratic leader,
has called for an investigation
of that.

26:41.066 --> 26:45.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it comes in the wake of a
Wall Street
Journal story last month that
reported about

26:45.337 --> 26:47.039 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stock trades that Tom Price had
done.

26:47.072 --> 26:48.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, watch this
space.

26:48.073 --> 26:49.208 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will see where that goes.

26:49.241 --> 26:56.248 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Susan Page, Tamara Keith, thank
you both.

26:56.281 --> 27:00.719 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SUSAN PAGE: Thank you.

27:00.752 --> 27:05.257 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: You're welcome.

27:05.290 --> 27:08.327 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

27:08.360 --> 27:13.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": the
difficult
political task of making Brexit
a reality;

27:13.532 --> 27:20.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
plus, when for-profit colleges
leave students
with no degree and a mountain of
debt.

27:20.105 --> 27:26.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But first: Painful divisions
that many Americans
thought the country had moved
past were brought

27:26.378 --> 27:29.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the surface after the recent
presidential
election.

27:29.781 --> 27:35.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, the Southern Poverty
Law Center has
been keeping a running tab on a
spike in hate

27:35.087 --> 27:37.189 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
incidents across the country.

27:37.222 --> 27:42.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Duarte
Geraldino reports
tonight from an area outside
Atlanta where

27:42.628 --> 27:48.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lingering racial scars are still
being examined
for lessons on how to move
forward.

27:48.500 --> 27:53.171 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And a warning: The story
contains some graphic
and offensive language.

27:53.205 --> 27:59.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: In 1987, race
and class
divisions erupted as
African-American leaders

27:59.845 --> 28:04.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and their supporters tried to
march through
Forsyth County, Georgia, an area
just 40 miles

28:04.950 --> 28:05.918 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
north of Atlanta.

28:05.951 --> 28:06.919 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PROTESTERS: Nigger, go home!

28:06.952 --> 28:08.854 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Nigger, go home!

28:08.887 --> 28:12.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OPRAH WINFREY, Host, "The Oprah
Winfrey Show":
Where do the people come from
who were shouting

28:12.691 --> 28:14.526 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
"Nigger, go home"?

28:14.560 --> 28:18.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: A moment of
extreme division
captured in one of Oprah
Winfrey's first shows.

28:18.964 --> 28:24.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She came to Forsyth after it was
thrust into
the global spotlight because an
unspoken ban

28:24.469 --> 28:30.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on black people was, all at
once, being exposed,
challenged and proudly defended.

28:30.576 --> 28:33.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANK SHIRLEY, Committee to Keep
Forsyth and
Dawson Counties White: My name
is Frank Shirley.

28:33.078 --> 28:36.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I am head of the Committee to
Keep Forsyth
Dawson County White.

28:36.114 --> 28:39.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were thousands of white
people that
came out to join our white
people's protest.

28:39.518 --> 28:40.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS, Author, "Blood
at the Root:
A Racial Cleansing in America":
First time

28:40.886 --> 28:44.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
anyone, including myself, had
seen black faces
in Forsyth County.

28:44.156 --> 28:48.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Yet there were
also whites
in the area, like Patrick
Phillips, who joined

28:48.894 --> 28:51.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
African-Americans to oppose the
ban.

28:51.263 --> 28:52.931 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He was just 17 at the time.

28:52.965 --> 28:56.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: All around me,
all of these
people started chanting "White
power."

28:56.902 --> 29:03.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at that point, I realize
that I had stumbled
my way into the middle of the
Klan's victory

29:03.742 --> 29:05.811 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
celebration for having stopped
the march.

29:05.844 --> 29:09.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: At that point,
what goes
through your mind?

29:09.948 --> 29:12.851 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: I was
horrified and kind
of shocked.

29:12.884 --> 29:16.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Phillips says
the march
came at a time when the
community was feeling

29:16.421 --> 29:21.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pressure from what it considered
outsiders,
a time when speaking up against
the racial

29:21.493 --> 29:23.328 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ban could make you a target.

29:23.362 --> 29:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: I still feel a
little bit
nervous talking about all of
this openly now.

29:28.233 --> 29:31.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: But, lately,
he's been doing
a lot of talking about his
childhood in North

29:31.937 --> 29:36.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Georgia and how his experience
can help all
Americans make sense of today.

29:36.508 --> 29:40.445 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: What's
happened in the last
couple of months, the ugliness
of the campaign,

29:40.479 --> 29:44.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the racial rhetoric and the
divisiveness,
and I think there are people who
want to interpret

29:44.916 --> 29:48.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that as a kind of wrong turning
in America.

29:48.654 --> 29:54.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think the other way to
interpret it is really
more of a revelation of some
currents that

29:54.226 --> 29:55.994 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have been there all along.

29:56.028 --> 29:58.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Phillips is
the author of
"Blood at the Root: A Racial
Cleansing in

29:58.930 --> 30:00.298 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
America."

30:00.332 --> 30:03.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The book is his way of making
sense of the
place where he grew up.

30:03.335 --> 30:07.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: The story that
I was told,
the myth, was very simple: White
people rose

30:07.773 --> 30:08.740 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
up.

30:08.774 --> 30:10.475 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They drove out their black
neighbors.

30:10.509 --> 30:13.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They were kept out for 100
years, what I now
know as the racial cleansing in
1912.

30:13.779 --> 30:16.948 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: We followed
his trail of
discovery.

30:16.982 --> 30:22.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It begins here at a cemetery
beside Pleasant
Grove Baptist Church just
outside of Cumming,

30:22.054 --> 30:23.021 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Georgia.

30:23.055 --> 30:24.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What is this?

30:24.256 --> 30:25.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: So, this is
the grave of
Mae Crow.

30:26.024 --> 30:29.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She comes into the story of
Forsyth County's
racial cleansing because, on
September 8,

30:29.995 --> 30:35.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
1912, she disappeared in the
woods about a
mile from her house, and all
hell broke loose

30:35.033 --> 30:37.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Forsyth County on the day of
Mae Crow's
funeral.

30:38.003 --> 30:42.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: According to
various accounts,
18-year-old Mae Crow is walking
alone in the

30:42.874 --> 30:47.946 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
woods when she's struck
repeatedly with a
rock, reportedly sexually
assaulted and left

30:47.979 --> 30:49.748 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for dead.

30:49.781 --> 30:52.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT, Grand Nice of
Mae Crow: She
was hit so hard that her eye was
dislodged

30:52.350 --> 30:55.120 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
from her skull and left hanging.

30:55.153 --> 30:58.957 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Debbie Vermaat
is Mae Crow's
grand niece.

30:58.990 --> 31:00.792 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She keeps a portrait of her in
her living
room.

31:00.826 --> 31:04.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: My grandmother
always said
that she was known to be the
prettiest girl

31:04.763 --> 31:05.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Forsyth County.

31:05.931 --> 31:08.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Word of the
attack spread
quickly.

31:08.500 --> 31:12.204 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Suspicion soon fell on a group
of young African-Americans.

31:12.237 --> 31:16.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Local media condemned them,
describing them
as the trio as -- quote -- "the
fiendish,

31:16.708 --> 31:19.177 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
low-browed, gorilla-type
Negroes."

31:19.211 --> 31:23.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Enraged by the news, a mob
immediately lynched
one man.

31:23.315 --> 31:27.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You believe that some of your
distant relatives
took part in this lynching?

31:27.052 --> 31:30.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: Yes, some of
them, I am fairly
sure they did.

31:30.756 --> 31:36.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These were the most aggrieved
and grieving
who wanted justice for what had
happened to

31:36.895 --> 31:38.597 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their loved one.

31:38.630 --> 31:42.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Two others,
both teenagers,
were arrested, tried, and
convicted.

31:42.801 --> 31:47.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A prominent doctor volunteered
land near his
home for the court-ordered
execution.

31:47.339 --> 31:50.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An estimated 5,000 people showed
up to watch
the hangings.

31:50.876 --> 31:55.080 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: Well, my
grandmother would've
been 18 months old sitting in
her mother's

31:55.113 --> 31:56.148 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
lap.

31:56.181 --> 31:57.783 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Watching
someone being lynched.

31:57.816 --> 31:59.551 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: Watching, right.

31:59.584 --> 32:04.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: So, do you
believe that
those three people, the two
teenagers, the

32:04.122 --> 32:06.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one young man in his 20s, do you
believe they
were innocent?

32:06.358 --> 32:08.026 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: I do believe
they were innocent.

32:08.059 --> 32:09.928 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I do believe.

32:09.961 --> 32:13.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I believe it's a huge cold
case that's
still sitting there to try to
figure out exactly

32:13.965 --> 32:15.734 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who did it.

32:15.767 --> 32:19.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Stories like
this were common
in the Jim Crow South, but what
was unique

32:19.504 --> 32:23.909 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in this case is what happened
next.

32:23.942 --> 32:28.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Newspapers of the day describe a
series of
late-night attacks on black
families, a campaign

32:28.079 --> 32:29.314 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of terror by whites.

32:29.347 --> 32:31.349 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: The Night
Riders won.

32:31.383 --> 32:32.851 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It worked.

32:32.884 --> 32:34.953 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They succeeded in their goal of
driving out
the entire black community.

32:34.986 --> 32:38.356 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: More than
1,000 African-Americans
banished.

32:38.390 --> 32:42.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: They largely
erased all
the signs that that community
had ever been

32:42.627 --> 32:44.095 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

32:44.129 --> 32:46.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At one point, this land belonged
to the black
community of Forsyth County.

32:46.998 --> 32:50.235 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: But not
everything was erased.

32:50.268 --> 32:55.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Phillips has spent 10 years
looking for physical
evidence of Forsyth's black
community, remains

32:55.607 --> 32:59.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of burned-out churches and lands
from which
African-Americans were driven
off.

32:59.678 --> 33:01.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Why is it so difficult to find
all this stuff?

33:01.813 --> 33:04.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: Well, I have a
land lot
number, and that's it.

33:04.850 --> 33:08.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Today, much of
this land
is high-priced real estate, but
when Phillips

33:08.620 --> 33:10.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
first came, it was a different
place.

33:10.856 --> 33:14.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: In 1977, when
my family
moved to Forsyth, the place was
changing quite

33:14.993 --> 33:16.761 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a bit.

33:16.795 --> 33:21.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The completion of Highway 400 in
the mid-1970s
suddenly made Forsyth viable as
a bedroom

33:21.366 --> 33:24.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
community for people, for
professional people
working in Atlanta.

33:24.402 --> 33:27.639 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Those
newcomers weren't
always welcome, though.

33:27.672 --> 33:32.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the time, fewer than 40,000
people lived
here, and some were willing to
use extreme

33:32.577 --> 33:35.513 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
measures to protect their way of
life.

33:35.547 --> 33:38.950 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today, more than 200,000 people
live in Forsyth.

33:38.984 --> 33:43.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And thanks to a surge in new
businesses and
high-paying jobs, it's one of
the wealthiest

33:43.688 --> 33:45.490 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
counties in the nation.

33:45.523 --> 33:52.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: To
successfully erase this
kind of land theft, to ignore
its impact over

33:52.530 --> 33:55.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
generations is really damaging.

33:55.333 --> 33:57.202 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Come on up, Duarte.

33:57.235 --> 34:01.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Phillips'
search did turn
up one major marker.

34:01.273 --> 34:05.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Remember the home of the wealthy
landowner
who volunteered his backyard for
the public

34:05.610 --> 34:07.946 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hangings in 1912?

34:07.979 --> 34:13.818 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's been meticulously restored,
and now houses
the local Chamber of Commerce.

34:13.852 --> 34:15.654 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
James McCoy is the chamber's
CEO.

34:15.687 --> 34:18.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES MCCOY, CEO, Forsyth
Chamber of Commerce:
You know, the events in --
particularly in

34:18.490 --> 34:22.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
1987, it was a soul-searching
moment for this
community.

34:22.994 --> 34:25.463 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Much of that was driven by the
business community.

34:25.497 --> 34:30.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Since 1987,
the Chamber's
membership has evolved, moving
from mostly

34:30.068 --> 34:35.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mom-and-pop businesses to larger
corporations
explicitly bound by the Civil
Rights Act of

34:35.707 --> 34:37.542 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
1964.

34:37.575 --> 34:41.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES MCCOY: We went from
probably a little
over 90 percent being
micro-enterprises, one

34:41.279 --> 34:50.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or two employees, to companies
that are more
in the mid-range of business of
anywhere between

34:50.755 --> 34:52.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
25 and 200 employees.

34:52.991 --> 34:58.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: You can
measure just how
far Forsyth has come by the
candidacy of Democrat

34:58.863 --> 35:00.265 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Daniel Blackman.

35:00.298 --> 35:04.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He ran to represent the county
in the Georgia
State Senate.

35:04.402 --> 35:11.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANIEL BLACKMAN, Former Georgia
State Senatorial
Candidate: I didn't win, but we
got 21 percent

35:11.109 --> 35:12.477 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the vote.

35:12.510 --> 35:15.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm almost positive to say
that some white
folks voted for me.

35:15.580 --> 35:21.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the fact that I'm in this
county, and we
were able to run, and I'm a
black candidate,

35:21.419 --> 35:26.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that really speaks
volumes, and it
shows that we are going in the
right direction.

35:26.224 --> 35:31.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Still, less
than 5 percent
of all Forsyth residents are
black.

35:31.363 --> 35:36.201 align:left position:25%,start line:80% size:75%
Yet, unlike many
African-Americans before
him, Blackman is vowing to stay.

35:36.234 --> 35:39.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He owns a strategic
communications business
and is raising his family here.

35:39.971 --> 35:43.208 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DANIEL BLACKMAN: I'm not going
anywhere for
a long time.

35:43.241 --> 35:49.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: But, for
Phillips and Vermaat,
the weight of their Forsyth
roots are too

35:49.080 --> 35:50.048 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
heavy.

35:50.081 --> 35:51.850 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Both moved up North decades ago.

35:51.883 --> 35:54.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK PHILLIPS: We were raised
with this
notion that, every day, America
gets a little

35:54.619 --> 35:59.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bit more just, every day, the
wheels of progress
kind of move forward.

35:59.357 --> 36:05.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, in the research, I
learned that
some -- what that leaves out is
that sometimes

36:05.797 --> 36:09.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the gains of one generation are
given back
in the next.

36:09.100 --> 36:11.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEBBIE VERMAAT: Because, down
there, nobody
wanted to talk about it.

36:11.369 --> 36:15.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DUARTE GERALDINO: Vermaat now
